            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_111gc' title='Col. 111GC &mdash; HL Deb 27 April 2004 vol 660 c111GC' name='column_111gc' href='#column_111gc' rel='bookmark'>111GC</a>
            question. When we come to appoint a traffic director, that is tine, but when it comes to costs, will that traffic director arrive with an army of people&#x2014;a large team that will have to be paid for&#x2014;or will he be on his own? For all we know, he might arrive with his 40 mates from the department to come and sort it out. If that is the case, will they all have to be paid for? Are we talking about one man or can this be a body of people? It would be helpful if the Minister could answer that.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0660P0-02854'>
        <a name='S5LV0660P0_20040427_GCR_251'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-matthew-evans' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
